</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<bibRefCitation author="Borrero, FJ" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 59" title="The Amphibulimidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Orthalicoidea) from Colombia and adjacent areas." volume="3054" year="2011">Borrero and Breure (2011)</bibRefCitation>
identified Ecuadorian material as this species, without having seen the type material. However, the type material of Sowerby is somewhat tapering at base and has the suture descending in front (Fig. 4
<normalizedToken originalValue="B–C">B-C</normalizedToken>
); also the shells figured by Borrero and Breure seem slightly smaller and slenderer. Therefore we are of the opinion that this taxon is best restricted to Peruvian material, and therefore the specimen figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="1 - 52" title="Annotated type catalogue of the Amphibulimidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Orthalicoidea) in the Natural History Museum, London." url="10.3897/zookeys.138.1847" volume="138" year="2011">Breure and Ablett (2011</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 20
<normalizedToken originalValue="A–C">A-C</normalizedToken>
) is now designated lectotype (design. n.). 
<taxonomicName authority="Scopoli, 1777" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1777" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimus pseudopiperatus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pseudopiperatus">Bulimus pseudopiperatus</taxonomicName>
J. Moricand, 1858 is considered a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Bulinidae" genus="Bulinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulinus piperitus" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="piperitus">Bulinus piperitus</taxonomicName>
Sowerby I, 1837. This was also the opinion of 
<bibRefCitation author="Weyrauch, WK" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Lilloana" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="457 - 499" title="Descripciones y notas sobre gastropodos terrestres de Venezuela, Colombia, Ecuador, Brasil y Peru." volume="21" year="1967">Weyrauch (1967)</bibRefCitation>
, who provided Pucallpa as the first precise locality for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
